 investments =E2=80=98generally receive favourable tax treatment and/or inv=
estment subsidies that make their risk and return characteristics different=
 than equity investments in general.=E2=80=99 In maintaining this treatment=
 for such investments, the Agencies also =E2=80=98recogniz[e]=E2=80=A6 the =
importance of these investments to promoting important public welfare goals=
=E2=80=A6.=E2=80=99 Such rationale would appear to apply equally to clean e=
