<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to think about the artificial intellig=
ence business is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everybody, by now,=C2=A0has an intuit=
ive understanding of how new software products are created in the US. New i=
deas in software come from visionary entrepreneurs who can work pretty chea=
p. You need a couple of engineers, some desks at a WeWork, some laptops, so=
me energy drinks,=C2=A0a modest=C2=A0cloud-computing budget. You build the =
thing, you try to find product-market fit, and if it works you scale rapidl=
y. The marginal cost of distributing one more copy of your app, or serving =
one more instance of your social media website, is basically zero. If your =
thing takes off, it can take off quickly, and it=E2=80=99s all profit.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everything in US tech finance is orien=
ted around that understanding. Talented tech workers want to be founders, b=
ecause founding your own company is the way to fame and riches in tech. Ven=
ture capital firms invest in risky early-stage software companies, because =
(1) those companies don=E2=80=99t need=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>much capital=
 to figure out if their idea works, and (2) if the idea=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0=
</em>work it will return many times the investment.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">Generative AI =E2=80=A6=C2=A0maybe does not work like tha=
t? It is extremely capital-intensive, by which I mean that you need a very=
=C2=A0<em>large=C2=A0</em>cloud computing budget to build and train an AI m=
odel that will do anything at all. And then scaling it is also quite expens=
ive; you need a ton more computing power to serve each new customer. Buildi=
ng an AI model is more like building a car than it is like building Faceboo=
k.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I asked you in the abstract =E2=80=9CI have=
 a potentially lucrative and important business idea, but it requires like =
$10 billion of startup capital and does not scale cheaply like software, ho=
w should I finance it,=E2=80=9D your first answer might not be =E2=80=9Cven=
ture capital.=E2=80=9D You=C2=A0might say something like =E2=80=9Cwell this=
 sounds like a big industrial project, what you should do is go get a job a=
t a big industrial company with a ton of money, and start a division there =
that will do this project.=E2=80=9D And if I said =E2=80=9Cwell it=E2=80=99=
s a tech idea,=E2=80=9D you=E2=80=99d say =E2=80=9Cah, even better, get a j=
ob at Google or Amazon or Alphabet, they have absolutely tons of money, mor=
e than they know what to do with, they can totally fund your $10 billion pr=
oject, no problem. Is it a virtual reality headset by any chance?=E2=80=9D=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the problem with AI is that it=C2=A0<em>is=
</em>, mostly, made in the Bay Area by tech-industry types, so it does defa=
ult to the startup mode, so you do have startups running around building AI=
. But to fund their billions of dollars of cloud computing costs, they=C2=
=A0</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">take billions of dollars of investmen=
t from cloud computing companies (Microsoft, Amazon, Alphabet),=C2=A0</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">take a lot of that investment in the f=
orm of cloud computing capacity rather than money, and=C2=A0</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">probably have=C2=A0<em>some=C2=A0</em>sort of un=
derstanding with those companies that there will be some commercial relatio=
nship between them, so that for instance Microsoft has rights to include Op=
enAI models in its software.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is a Silicon Valley-style compromise betwee=
n =E2=80=9Call new software must be built by startups=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=
=9Cactually giant companies with tons of money and smart employees=C2=A0and=
 complementary capabilities probably do have some advantage in building thi=
s particular expensive thing.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/34162107.258396/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMjIvc2hhcmVob2xkZXJzLWFyZS1wZW9wbGUtdG9vP2NtcGlkPUJC=
