yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEyOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB7ec77490" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  talked about this dynamic last week</a>, in part =
because Silicon Valley venture capitalists have been complaining about it: =
=E2=80=9CMANG=E2=80=9D (Microsoft, Amazon, Nvidia, and Google/Alphabet) hav=
e been some of the biggest investors in AI startups, and have advantages ov=
er traditional VCs in making these investments (mainly that they get to mak=
e them in the form of computing power), and the traditional VCs feel a bit =
priced out.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Others also have complaints. If Microsoft had =
just announced one day =E2=80=9Cwe are going to build large language models=
 to incorporate into our search engine and Office suite, we hired a bunch o=
f people, we gave them a lot of computing power, away we go,=E2=80=9D well =
=E2=80=A6 I don=E2=80=99t want to say that would be <em>no problem=C2=A0</e=
