 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">incredible numbers here</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Byju=E2=80=99s, the world=E2=80=99s most valua=
ble edtech startup, has cut its valuation ask by 99% in a rights issue it l=
aunched Monday as the Indian firm works to address its working capital need=
s. The startup is looking to raise $200 million in the rights issue, capita=
l it said was =E2=80=9Cessential to prevent any further value impairment.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The startup, once India=E2=80=99s most valuabl=
e, is resetting its valuation to =E2=80=9Cnext to nothing=E2=80=9D in the r=
ights issue, where all existing investors have an opportunity to participat=
e, according to a source familiar with the matter. If Byju=E2=80=99s succee=
ds in raising $200 million, the post-money valuation of the startup will be=
 in the range of $220 million to $225 million, a 99% drop from the $22 bill=
ion value that the startup had attained in 2022, according to the source, w=
ho requested anonymity sharing nonpublic information.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Byju=E2=80=99s founder Byju Raveendran told sh=
areholders in a letter Monday that he and other founders of the edtech grou=
p have invested $1.1 billion into the Bengaluru-headquartered startup in th=
e last 18 months and seek continued support from the investors to keep the =
business afloat. =E2=80=9CWe have made immense personal sacrifices for the =
sake of the company. We have spent our lives building this company and are =
fervent believers in its mission,=E2=80=9D Raveendran wrote in the letter, =
seen by TechCrunch. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The rights issue comes as Byju=E2=80=99s looks=
 to secure capital amid a severe funding crunch. The startup, which spent $=
2.5 billion acquiring more than a dozen firm in 2021 and 2022, has raised m=
ore than $5 billion in equity and debt from backers including Peak XV, Ligh=
tspeed, Chan Zuckerberg Initiative, BlackRock, UBS, Prosus Ventures and B C=
apital. Byju=E2=80=99s said in a statement that it expects the rights issue=
 to close in 30 days.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last week Bloomberg <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34162107.258396/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMjMvYnlqdS1zLXRvLXNsYXNoLTIyLWJpbGxpb24=
tdmFsdWF0aW9uLWJ5LTkwLXRvLXJhaXNlLWZyZXNoLWZ1bmRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMjkyNF9NT0=
5FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtP=
TI0MDEyOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB88a99447=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> reported</a> a 90% cut =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ca price that valu=
es the firm at less than $2 billion, =E2=80=A6 down from $22 billion at its=
 previous round in late 2022=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I guess things are=
 moving fast, and in the wrong direction? On these numbers, the people who =
put in $5 billion back in the good times will own less than 10% of the comp=
any, while the people who put in $200 million in the bad times will own 90%=
.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The point of a rights offering is to be coerci=
ve: Existing investors have the right to put more money in at the rights pr=
ice, which here is basically zero, and if they don=E2=80=99t put more money=
 in then they get diluted by the people who do. Here, if you put up $1 bill=
ion for 5% of the company back when it was worth $20 billion, Byju=E2=80=99=
s will come to you and ask you to put in $10 million more to keep your 5% s=
take; if you say no, you=E2=80=99ll be diluted down to about 0.5%. If you=
=E2=80=99ve already thrown away $1 billion, what=E2=80=99s $10 million more=
? On the other hand, if Byju=E2=80=99s has already reduced your $1 billion =
investment to zero, why would you give them any more money? Getting diluted=
 doesn=E2=80=99t matter if the stock is going to zero; owning 5% of a compa=
ny worth zero is no better than owning 0.5% of it. The main questions in th=
e rights offering are: Do you trust that the company has a plan to turn thi=
ngs around, and that this one last contribution is enough to see it through=
? And also: How mad are you about what happened to the rest of your money?<=
/p>
